description:
Atmosphere;
When walking into Pagan Idol, it feels like we're walking into a wooden ship. Continuing on walking towards the back, we pass through a door and it turns into an night time island theme. It's kind of dark with lots of colorful lights and tropical decorations everywhere. Every 10 minutes or so, there's a deep voice that plays on the speakers and some fog gets blown out really intensely, like a fire-breathing dragon blowing out smoke.

Service;
Service is a bit slow. We could be standing right in front of the bartender for 5 minutes and it'll feel like we're being ignored, but they're actually busy making the complicated tiki drinks for someone else.

Drinks;
I got the scorpion bowls and the house daiquiri. The scorpion bowls were good, shared it with 3-4 people. Got a few of those and ended up with a slight hangover the next morning. The house daiquiri was good too, but I felt like it was 90% ice and 10% alcohol in the glass. (See attached photos.)

Overall;
This is a nice little tiki bar in the Financial district. Good to come here after work with some coworkers.
